profile.description:
An inner-city community like no other, Richmond is known for its proximity to the city, its multicultural heritage, its plethora of pubs and its claim to fame as the “sporting capital of Australia”. 
Flanked by Victoria Street, the heart of the Vietnamese community and affectionately known as “Little Saigon”, and Swan Street, the entry to a multitude of sporting and event venues, the suburb is also renown for Church Street, home to fashionable furniture and design stores. 
Life in Richmond is busy, energetic and fun. Begin your day with a cycle along the Yarra River, followed by breakfast at Top Paddock before taking that short commute to work. After work, stop by one of the many pubs in Richmond, catch a gig at the Corner and be home in time for a good night’s sleep. 
A traditionally working-class area, Richmond has developed as a rich mix of lifestyles and cultures. If you like to be in the centre of the action, Richmond could be the view for you.
profile.headline: An inner-city oasis, Richmond is loved by young and old for its heritage, location and community feel
